  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rural Shelter in the South of Haiti</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">La pr&#xE9;sente action vise, de mani&#xE8;re g&#xE9;n&#xE9;rale &#xE0; contribuer &#xE0; am&#xE9;liorer l&#x2019;habitat et les conditions de  logement des familles vuln&#xE9;rables dans le Sud. De mani&#xE8;re sp&#xE9;cifique, l&#x2019;action vise &#xE0; :

-Awareness raising of habitants and accompaniers to defend their rights to shelter;  
- Training and capacity building in construction techniques to empower and contribute  to a skilled local labor force in the region that can build houses to resist disaster
- Assist vulnerable families to access decent housing (construction of 2 model homes in collaboration with Habitat for Humanity
-Organisational Capacity Strengthening</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">vulnerable people in Chantal, Torbeck and Camp Perrin have improved capacity to advocate for improved housing conditions which is intended to improve their access to better shelter. Two families have access to safe shelter built according to standards and norms. Skilled laborers available in the area to continue to build staff resistant homes which protect families during storms and hurricanes; therefore reducing their vulnerability.</narrative>
  </description>
